    {
      "type": "html",
      "text": "\nFor example, in this C function, <i>printf</i> and <i>phase_shift</i> are free variables.  The first is a standard library function; the second had better be defined by the programmer; else this function is in error.  <i>angle</i>, being a formal parameter, is not a free variable; nor is <i>x</i>.  \nThe first use of <i>sin</i> is a [[Free Variable]]; it too is a standard library function (one which returns the sine of the angle).   The second use of <i>sin</i> (in the if statement) is not, as a local definition for <i>sin</i> is provided (which shadows the library function).  ",
      "id": "622ed4f2299f2c63a9873d43bab8b9f9"
    },
